- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing movie scripts and identifying missing components in the Bechdel test using natural language processing techniques.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category as the paper uses machine learning techniques like Principal Component Analysis to analyze the movie scripts.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses machine learning techniques to analyze the data.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper discusses the representation of women in films and its impact on society.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the representation of women in films and its impact on social networks.
